Description: (Repeat)POST FLIGHT INSPECTION FOUND BLUE FLUID LEAKING FROM MAST UNDERNEATH BELLY NEAR BAGGAGE DOOR FLUID IS ALL OVER BELLY AND UP THE TAIL CONE
CorrectiveActionNotes:
CONFIRMED DISCREPANCY. BEGAN TROUBLESHOOTING BY REMOVING PANELS 313DC, 313CC, 313BC, 313AL AND 313AR TO 
ACCESS AND VISUALLY INSPECT LAVATORY SYSTEM FILL AND DRAIN DUCTING. FOUND NO VISIBLE DISCREPANCIES ON ANY DUCTING OR FITTINGS. 
COULD NOT LOCATE ANY SIGN OF LEAKAGE ALONG THE RH SIDE OF THE AIRCRAFT WHERE ALL THE PLUMBING IS FOR THE LAVATORY FILL AND DRAIN 
SYSTEM. UPON FURTHER INSPECTION FOUND ALL THE LAVATORY FLUID WAS CONCENTRATED TO THE LH SIDE OF THE AIRCRAFT COMING OUT OF THE 
VENT DRAIN. WHILE PANEL REMOVED FOUND BLUE FLUID RESIDUE AROUND INSIDE THE COMPARTMENT. PROCEEDED TO CLEAN ALL FLUID OFF OF THE
WIRING , WALLS AND FLIGHT CONTROL CABLES. FOUND THAT THERE WAS A CLAMP MISSING FROM THE VENT DRAIN HEATER, MAKING THE FLUID GO 
BACK INTO THE COMPARTMENT INSTEAD OF OVERBOARD. ONCE CLEANED PROCEED TO INSPECT THE LAVATORY AREA. REMOVED THE TOILET COVER 
ASSEMBLY TO ACCES THE TOILET ASSEMBLY FOR DETAILED INSPECTION PER CESSNA CITATION 560XL AMM 38-30-00. REMOVED PANEL 261HC TO 
VISUALLY INSPECT THE TOILET VENT DRAIN LINE OF ANY DISCREPANCY. FOUND NO VISIBLE DISCREPANCY OF ANY FLUID SPILL ALONG THE TOILET 
VENT DRAIN LINE. REINSTALLED PANEL 261HC. REMOVED THE TOILET FRAME TO LIFT UP THE TOILET BOWL ASSEMBLY AND INSPECTED THE DRAIN 
LINE PLUG SEALS FOR ANY DISCREPANCIES. FOUND THE SEAL TO BE SERVICEABLE AND NO VISIBLE LEAKAGE AROUND THE SEAL OR UNDERNEATH THE 
TOILET ASSEMBLY. RESEATED THE TOILET BOWL ASSEMBLY. DECIDED TO STICK HAND INSIDE THE TOILET BOWL TO FEEL AROUND FOR ANY CRACKS.
